<paragraph id="1D39F423FC033C656E8AFF19FBC1FED2" blockId="13.[140,1108,167,334]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">
This species is known from northeastern 
<collectingRegion id="DF423AC1FC033C656C5FFF19FD42FF5E" box="[601,692,167,193]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Arizona</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="DF423AC1FC033C656CC6FF19FD0AFF5E" box="[704,764,167,193]" country="United States of America" name="Utah" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Utah</collectingRegion>
, northern 
<collectingRegion id="DF423AC1FC033C656D75FF19FBF0FF5E" box="[883,1030,167,193]" country="United States of America" name="New Mexico" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">New Mexico</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="DF423AC1FC033C656A14FF19FF34FF7B" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Colorado</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="DF423AC1FC033C656F02FF74FE8EFF7B" box="[260,376,202,228]" country="United States of America" name="Wyoming" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Wyoming</collectingRegion>
. It is characterized by a shiny, slightly more cordate pronotum than other members of the group, without notable basal punctuation, relatively flat elytral intervals, with small punctures in the elytral striae, and distinctive male genitalia. As first revisers, we choose 
<taxonomicName id="DA868FA0FC033C656FFCFE8AFD34FED1" authority="Casey" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" box="[506,706,307,334]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sarpedon">
<emphasis id="2FF22831FC033C656FFCFE8AFD8FFED2" box="[506,633,307,333]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">B. sarpedon</emphasis>
Casey
</taxonomicName>
as the valid name of this species.
</paragraph>
